bug.short_desc: Some Gtk widgets blend into the background

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
For some apps (virt-manager and anaconda in particular) text input fields, drop down lists, etc are not clearly visible. They don't have a border and their background color is grey blending into the rest of the UI of the application. See the attached screenshot.
OTOH other apps appear to be just fine. In the example mate-screenshot.
I've tried running both as root and also virt-manager as root and non-root, doesn't seem to have any difference. The next thing I can think of is that both virt-manager and anaconda are actually written in Python and use glade files to define their interface. Could that be the reason ?
At this point I have no idea which component is to blame so please reassign if necessary or let me know what other info to provide.
I'm using the MATE desktop environment.
